1 resilience and long-term stability; and
2 WHEREAS, the profession works to reduce barriers that limit opportunity, promote
3 respectful dialogue, and support policies and practices that empower clients; and
4 WHEREAS, social workers promote safety and positive outcomes when providing
5 care and coordination of care for clients experiencing mental health conditions, substance
6 abuse, or family instability, including child welfare concerns; and
7 WHEREAS, this year's theme for social worker month is "Social Workers: Uplift.
8 Defend. Transform.", shining a light on the resolute spirit of social workers who transform
9 lives while bringing hope and healing to the communities they serve.
10 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
11 does hereby designate Monday, April 13, 2026, as Social Work Day at the Louisiana State
12 Capitol and does hereby commend and celebrate, along with the National Association of
13 Social Workers, social workers across the state who uplift, defend, and positively transform
14 the lives of individuals and communities in Louisiana.
